  "text": "Theorem 1 is significant in that, for large T , it improves the regret dependence from S to √ S, compared to the best known bound of [CITATION_1] . The main intuition for this improved S-dependence is that we bound the estimation error of the next-state value function directly, instead of the transition probabilities.",
